title: $:/plugins/rimir/present/layouts
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Layouts

Each slide's layout is selected by the `mm.slide-layout` field (or whichever field you pass as `layout-field=`). The named value resolves to `$:/plugins/rimir/present/layouts/<name>` — drop in your own tiddler with that title to author new layouts.

|!Name |!Effect |!Slide-side fields read |
|`default` |Caption + body. The fallback when no layout is set or the named layout doesn't exist. |`caption`, `text` |
|`title` |Big centered caption with the body shown smaller below. For intro / section-divider slides. |`caption`, `text` |
|`two-column` |Two equal columns. Reads `mm.slide-left` / `mm.slide-right` if present (wikitext), otherwise the entire `text` body fills the left column. |`caption`, `mm.slide-left`, `mm.slide-right`, `text` |
|`quote` |Pull-quote with optional attribution. The body becomes the quote. |`text`, `caption`, `mm.slide-attribution` |
|`image` |Image at top, caption + body below. |`mm.slide-image` (image src), `caption`, `text` |
|`full` |No chrome — body fills the stage. Use for custom-CSS slides. |`text` |

!! Authoring a new layout

Create a tiddler named `$:/plugins/rimir/present/layouts/<name>` of type `text/vnd.tiddlywiki`. Inside, you can read the slide's fields via `<<currentTiddler>>` and `{{!!field-name}}`. The widget wraps the layout in `<$tiddler tiddler=<<slide>>>` before transcluding, so all field references resolve against the active slide automatically.

Example skeleton:

```
title: $:/plugins/rimir/present/layouts/bullets

\procedure render-bullets()
<div class="rr-present-layout my-bullets-layout">
<h2>{{!!caption}}</h2>
<$transclude $mode="block"/>
</div>
\end render-bullets

<$transclude $variable="render-bullets"/>
```

Then set `mm.slide-layout=bullets` on slides that should use it.
